# Anything in this file is excluded from the build context sent to the
# Docker daemon. Aim is to keep the context small so the build is fast and
# never accidentally bundles secrets or local-only state into the image.

# Per-package node_modules. Docker reinstalls everything inside the build
# stage anyway via `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`.
**/node_modules

# Build outputs. The image's build stage produces these fresh.
**/dist
**/build

# Test output. `vitest run --coverage` writes a whole HTML report tree that the
# image has no use for. Keep in sync with .gitignore's `coverage`.
**/coverage

# Git metadata.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / OS noise.
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
**/*.swp

# Logs and local-only state. `**/` so a nested log (e.g. a package dir) is
# excluded too, not just one dropped at the context root.
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# Local Claude Code state (settings.local.json permission allowlists, etc.) —
# local-only, exactly the kind of state this file's preamble excludes. `**/`
# so a package-level .claude/ is caught as well.
**/.claude/

# Secrets. The app needs no env vars, so any such file is local-only by
# definition — but `COPY . .` would still pull it into build-stage layers
# (which leak via pushed intermediate layers or registry-backed build
# caches) if someone drops one in the repo. `**/`-prefixed so a NESTED secret
# (e.g. services/ai-bridge/.env — the one package that IS env-configured, or
# an artifacts/dm-screen/dev.key) is excluded too: a bare `.env` pattern
# matches only the context root, which is the exact leak this list exists to
# prevent.
#
# Tradeoff: these are secret/cert-shaped names (crypto key & cert extensions,
# dotenv files, a `secrets*` prefix) that no source artifact in this workspace
# uses, and the `**/` makes them shadow such a file at ANY depth. If someone
# ever DID name real source with one of these (e.g. src/secretsManager.ts, a
# *.key fixture), `COPY . .` would silently omit it and the image build would
# fail — but that failure is loud and immediate, and keeping a would-be secret
# out of build-stage layers is the priority. Narrowing these back to the
# context root would reopen the nested-secret leak this block exists to close.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx
**/secrets*

# Docker scaffolding (no point shipping the Dockerfile into the image).
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml

# Project intake docs — not needed inside the image. CLAUDE.md, README,
# the handover docs, etc. stay in the repo but don't bloat the build
# context. Glob the HANDOVER-*.md set so new handover docs are excluded
# without having to touch this file each time one is added.
HANDOVER-*.md
CLAUDE.md
MANUAL-TESTS-*.md
# Design specs and other written-for-humans material. Directory-wide so a new
# spec doesn't have to be listed here one file at a time.
docs/

# Data-generation script outputs that aren't part of the source tree
# (lib/ was deleted in Phase 3, but cover .pnpm-store just in case).
.pnpm-store
